        rdfs:comment        "PECAM-1/CD31 is a member of the immunoglobulin superfamily (IgSF) and has been implicated to mediate the adhesion and trans-endothelial migration of T-lymphocytes into the vascular wall, T cell activation and angiogenesis. It has six Ig homology domains within its extracellularly and an ITIM motif within its cytoplasmic region. PECAM-1 mediates cellular interactions by both homophilic and heterophilic interactions. The cytoplasmic domain of PECAM-1 contains tyrosine residues which serves as docking sites for recruitment of cytosolic signaling molecules. Under conditions of platelet activation, PECAM-1 is phosphorylated by Src kinase members. The tyrosine residues 663 and 686 are required for recruitment of the SH2 domain containing PTPs." ;
        rdfs:label          "PECAM1 interactions" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: de Bono, B, Garapati, P V, 2008-02-26 12:30:30" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Trowsdale, J, 2008-02-26 12:02:59" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-210990" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-202733/R-HSA-202733> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

